constructor.details: Sets the values for {owner}, require contract {reserve} balance of 0.1 ether, initialize {peanuts} with a default value of 2,000 and {txCheckLock} with default value of false.

deposit().details: Deposits are made to the contract before any interaction with it. Only valid when the contract hasn't been hacked.

getContractBalance().details: Returns the balance of the contract.

getMyBalance().details: Returns the balance of any address that has deposited to the contract.

getPeanuts(uint256).details: Gets[buys] peanuts from the contract[Vending Machine]. Only valid when the contract hasn't been hacked. Requirements: - The caller must have deposited to contract and has a balance of at least `units` of peanuts to buy. - The contract must have enough peanuts in stock a caller wants to buy/get.

getPeanutsBalance().details: Returns the amount of peanuts remaining in the contract[Vending Machine].

getReserveAmount().details: Returns the amount the owner deposited to the contract as reserve.

hasNotBeenHacked().details: Returns the opposite truthy value of txCheckLock Can only be called by the current owner.

restockPeanuts(uint256).details: Restocks the amount of peanuts in the contract[Vending Machine], increasing the total supply. Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawal().details: Withdraws deposit or balance from the contract. Only valid when the contract hasn't been hacked. Requirements: - The caller must have deposited to contract and has a balance in the contract even after transaction.
